result.name: So Thai So Good (尖沙咀)

reviews.text: This restaurant is among the best Thai restaurants out there in Hong Kong. The service was excellent and the waiters greeted us politely. The price was reasonable and not too over-priced. You might be overwhelmed by the number of dishes they offer - it took us 7 mins just to finish reading all the options once. I think the hidden gem in this restaurant has got to be the fried rice with seafood and prawn in coconut milk - it’s THE BEST Thai fried rice I’ve ever tried. It had vibrant flavours with fresh seafood. The restaurant itself is spacious and has plenty of seats. One thing that I was not quite satisfied was the noise. Perhaps there were too many customers so it was as noisy as in a wet market. This could be avoided by eating in a non-peak hour. I would definitely recommend this to anyone who wish to try some exotic flavours.
This was  the second time I went here.The set lunch was amazing. The chicken was tender and even the tea set was decent. The environment was OK. It is a place that I would highly recommend.

ordered grilled pork neck and red curry. The pork neck was tough and rubbery, enormous effort was required to chew into bits. Worst ever in my life. Red curry was just nothing special. I had expected higher quality for the prices charged. Will not visit again.

A great place to  have a blast with Thai food, the staff were nice and treated me and my friend that visited me from USA good.
The foods are so delicious and affordable.
Its a quiet place to chill with friends and family.
Food is average. As a thai food lover it's definitely a no.
